reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works over the sink or in the cupboards too!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the 2 Tier Expandable Cabinet Shelf Organizer for under my kitchen sink, and I'm absolutely thrilled with the results! This organizer has transformed the chaos under my sink into a well-organized and efficient space.The 8 detachable panels provided me with customization options I didn't even know I needed. I was able to adjust the shelves to fit around pipes and other obstacles, maximizing the available space. The panels are sturdy and well-made, so I don't have to worry about them breaking or bending under the weight of my cleaning supplies and other items.Installation was a breeze; no tools required. The expandable design allowed me to find the perfect fit for my cabinet without any hassle. The black color adds a sleek touch to the space, making it look even more organized and clean.What truly impressed me was the multi-use aspect of this organizer. While I initially purchased it for my kitchen, I found it to be equally useful under the bathroom sink. The two tiers provide ample storage space, and I'm now able to keep all my essentials neatly arranged and easily accessible.In terms of durability, this organizer has exceeded my expectations. It's been a few months since I installed it, and there's been no wobbling, sagging, or signs of wear and tear. The materials used are clearly of high quality.If you're looking to tame the clutter under your sink and optimize your storage space, I highly recommend the 2 Tier Expandable Cabinet Shelf Organizer. It's versatile, well-built, and aesthetically pleasing. I couldn't be happier with this purchase!

reviews.reviewText: I got this for under my kitchen sink. It fits great & can be adjusted to fit cupboard width. Can also set up the shelves closer or farther apart. Very easy to set up & sturdy. I just ordered another one for my bathroom cupboard.

Incredibly easy to assemble - comes with all parts and the “Allen key” for the screws. Takes 10 minutes to put together and you’re done! I ordered 2 and used both for under-sink storage. Will be buying another for my daughter’s bathroom!** using as a MUCH more affordable option than the “pull out” cart style under sink tier trays**5 STARS!

I’m very impressed with this rack. I have a similar design one I got years ago that’s plastic and chipping apart. However, the frame of this one is all metal, and it’s attached with screws (tool provided) instead of clips that break over time.It is sturdy enough to hold a lot of heavy cleaning supplies.
